   Data Centers and Institutions holding Arctic Datasets
     * United Nations Environmental Program's Global Resource Information
       Database (GRID)
     * Food and Agriculture Organization of the UN - On-line multi-lingual
       databases
     * Statistics Norway
     * NOAA's National Geophysical Data Center (NGDC)
     * Russian Federation Service's Arctic and Antarctic Research
       Institute
     * WMO Global Digital Sea Ice Data Bank (GDSIDB)
     * University of Hawaii Sea Level Center
     * Global Change Master Directory
     * World Resources 1996-1997 Report prepared for the UN, World Bank,
       etc.
     * Center for International Earth Science Information Network (CIESIN)
     * Open Directory web project
     * Canada Fisheries and Oceans Statistical Services
     * Canadian Forestry researchers directory
     * Canadian National Forestry Database Program
     * Natural Resources Canada
     * NOAA's National Oceanographic Data Center
     * NOAA's National Climatic Data Center
     * National Data Buoy Center
     * Canadian Meteorological Center (CMC)
     * International Arctic Data Directory (ADD)
     * Greenland Climate Network
     * National Snow and Ice Data Center
     * Arctic System Science (ARCSS) Data Coordination Center (ADCC)
     * NOAA's PMEL EPIC Hydrographic and Time Series Data On-line
     * UCAR/NOAA Joint Office for Science Support - on-line data
     * NASA Langley Atmospheric Sciences Data Center - on-line data
     * Arctic and Antarctic Research Institute / Russian Federal Service
       For Hydrometeorology and Environmental Monitoring
     * National Ice Core Laboratory
     * Canadian Ice Service
     * The Arctic and Antarctic Research Center
     * Sea Ice analysis for the Arctic and Antarctica at the National Ice
       Center.


